cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.CL 

This paper deals with image generation and translation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The method presented involves training a network to imitate the mapping of high-level constructs to pixels, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses applications in image segmentation, which is a topic in computer graphics (cs.GR) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
